>From: "Curt Conklin" <CONKLINC(-at-)lawgate.byu.edu>
>Date: Mon, 11 Nov 2002 12:44:22 -0700
>
>While winching away at the stubborn filter, I noticed a huge screwdriver
>slotted plug immediately to the right of the center of the engine on the
>very back edge and corner of the central block.  What in the (-at-)#$%! is that?

It's on the bottom surface of the crankcase, facing up, right?  That's the
cover for the oil pressure relief valve.  Basically it lets the engine oil
bypass the oil cooler when the oil is really cold.  Muir and Bentley both
have pictures and discussion.

Matt Roberds
